WEEK – 12
Question 1

Question:
Write a Java program to create three threads:

1st thread displays GOOD MORNING every 1 second

2nd thread displays HELLO every 2 seconds

3rd thread displays WELCOME every 3 seconds

Program
class GoodMorning extends Thread {
    public void run() {
        try {
            while(true) {
                System.out.println("GOOD MORNING");
                Thread.sleep(1000);
            }
        } catch(Exception e) { }
    }
}

class Hello extends Thread {
    public void run() {
        try {
            while(true) {
                System.out.println("HELLO");
                Thread.sleep(2000);
            }
        } catch(Exception e) { }
    }
}

class Welcome extends Thread {
    public void run() {
        try {
            while(true) {
                System.out.println("WELCOME");
                Thread.sleep(3000);
            }
        } catch(Exception e) { }
    }
}

class Main {
    public static void main(String args[]) {
        GoodMorning t1 = new GoodMorning();
        Hello t2 = new Hello();
        Welcome t3 = new Welcome();

        t1.start();
        t2.start();
        t3.start();
    }
}

Output
GOOD MORNING
HELLO
WELCOME
GOOD MORNING
GOOD MORNING
HELLO
WELCOME
...

Explanation:

Each thread runs independently and sleeps for a specific time using Thread.sleep().

Question 2

Question:
Implement the above program by assigning priorities to threads such that:

1st thread executes first

then 2nd thread

then 3rd thread

Program
class ThreadPriority extends Thread {

    public ThreadPriority(String name) {
        super(name);
    }

    public void run() {
        System.out.println("Running thread: " + Thread.currentThread().getName());
    }

    public static void main(String args[]) {

        ThreadPriority t1 = new ThreadPriority("GOOD MORNING");
        ThreadPriority t2 = new ThreadPriority("HELLO");
        ThreadPriority t3 = new ThreadPriority("WELCOME");

        t1.setPriority(Thread.MAX_PRIORITY);
        t2.setPriority(Thread.NORM_PRIORITY);
        t3.setPriority(Thread.MIN_PRIORITY);

        t1.start();
        t2.start();
        t3.start();
    }
}

Output (may vary)
Running thread: GOOD MORNING
Running thread: HELLO
Running thread: WELCOME

Explanation:

Thread priority decides execution preference, not guarantee.

MAX_PRIORITY → highest

NORM_PRIORITY → normal

MIN_PRIORITY → lowest
